1
00:00:00,212 --> 00:00:01,601
Previously on Jericho

2
00:00:01,949 --> 00:00:03,164
<i>Bring them inside.</i>

3
00:00:03,318 --> 00:00:04,649
<i>Some of them were on planes</i>

4
00:00:04,650 --> 00:00:06,559
<i>that landed in
the middle of nowhere.</i>

5
00:00:06,772 --> 00:00:08,373
<i>They've been walking
for weeks.</i>

6
00:00:08,682 --> 00:00:10,389
<i>They must have gone
through hell.</i>

7
00:00:10,390 --> 00:00:13,381
<i>Oh, my God... Roger.</i>

8
00:00:14,049 --> 00:00:16,460
<i>You have moderate frostbite
on your toes and fingers.</i>

9
00:00:16,461 --> 00:00:18,120
<i>You need to keep
them clean and warm.</i>

10
00:00:18,196 --> 00:00:19,740
<i>Do you know anyone
in Jericho?</i>

11
00:00:19,914 --> 00:00:22,152
<i>Actually... I do.</i>

12
00:00:23,822 --> 00:00:24,921
<i>Hello, Rob.</i>

13
00:00:25,192 --> 00:00:27,449
<i>We're using the generator
to power the town hall</i>

14
00:00:27,450 --> 00:00:29,793
<i>for three hours a day,
the Med Center for six.</i>

15
00:00:29,994 --> 00:00:33,352
<i>With 53 new people, at current
levels of consumption...</i>

16
00:00:33,773 --> 00:00:37,149
<i>we will be completely out
of gas and diesel in two weeks.</i>

17
00:00:37,341 --> 00:00:39,868
<i>- Mrs. Green?
- What?</i>

18
00:00:40,081 --> 00:00:41,884
<i>Eric told me that
April's pregnant.</i>

19
00:00:42,203 --> 00:00:43,572
<i>It's the Old Man.</i>

20
00:00:43,820 --> 00:00:46,174
<i>He's coming for us
using us against each other.</i>

21
00:00:46,232 --> 00:00:49,377
<i>We go see him and if,
if he is behind this,</i>

22
00:00:49,589 --> 00:00:50,592
<i>We take him out.</i>

23
00:00:50,650 --> 00:00:52,483
<i>We leave first thing
in the morning.</i>

24
00:01:18,049 --> 00:01:19,573
<i>Any luck out there?</i>

25
00:01:19,747 --> 00:01:21,001
Sorry, ma'am.

26
00:01:24,165 --> 00:01:26,364
Nothing?
Not even rabbits?

27
00:01:26,904 --> 00:01:28,523
Never seen anything
like it before.

28
00:01:28,524 --> 00:01:29,952
Nothing moving out there.

29
00:01:30,119 --> 00:01:33,379
Think it was the fallout? Maybe it was
the radiation that killed the deer.

30
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:35,269
There'd still be dead animals,
carcasses, something.

31
00:01:35,270 --> 00:01:36,114
I mean, it was weird.

32
00:01:36,115 --> 00:01:37,373
Like all the game had vanished.

33
00:01:37,670 --> 00:01:38,673
How far out
did you go?

34
00:01:38,712 --> 00:01:42,378
15 miles out by Mill Pond
along the creek there.

35
00:01:42,498 --> 00:01:44,422
Guess we're going to have
to drive, huh, Jake?

36
00:01:44,423 --> 00:01:47,435
Yeah, but we have to be careful
about burning the gas rations

37
00:01:47,436 --> 00:01:48,438
in the middle of winter.

38
00:01:48,496 --> 00:01:50,424
We need everything we can
to run the generator.

39
00:01:50,425 --> 00:01:51,987
We can live without
power for now.

40
00:01:52,528 --> 00:01:53,715
Make fires to stay warm.

41
00:01:54,091 --> 00:01:56,136
But we won't see Spring
if we don't eat.

42
00:01:56,213 --> 00:01:59,117
Stanley and I will have to use
whatever gas we can spare.

43
00:01:59,357 --> 00:02:01,314
and go out west,
Go out as far as it takes.

44
00:02:01,315 --> 00:02:04,122
The rest of the hunting parties
will have to scrounge around locally.

45
00:02:04,123 --> 00:02:06,142
Yeah, and Mimi's coming
with us.

46
00:02:07,068 --> 00:02:07,868
What?

47
00:02:09,210 --> 00:02:12,113
Well, in case something happens to me,
I want to make sure she knows...

48
00:02:12,132 --> 00:02:13,535
how to trap and shoot, okay?

49
00:02:16,676 --> 00:02:19,300
Look, the further you get
the hairier the roads are.

50
00:02:19,338 --> 00:02:20,824
With food being
as scarce as it is,

51
00:02:20,825 --> 00:02:22,598
there's bound to be
some trouble out there.

52
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:24,914
That sleeping bag's
rated to 40 below

53
00:02:25,034 --> 00:02:28,077
and here's a wind-proof lighter for you.
You're going to need them both.

54
00:02:28,424 --> 00:02:29,509
Good hunting.

55
00:02:32,403 --> 00:02:34,409
I'm guessing the good folks
of Jericho don't know

56
00:02:34,410 --> 00:02:37,361
about all this stuff down here.
- They don't know about a lot of things.

57
00:02:37,517 --> 00:02:39,634
That'll be enough to get us
to the Old Man's place?

58
00:02:39,635 --> 00:02:41,732
He is only about
two hours away.

59
00:02:41,901 --> 00:02:43,734
I didn't realize
he was so close.

60
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:45,374
He chose the rally point.

61
00:02:45,846 --> 00:02:47,534
Wanted it in his backyard.

62
00:02:47,535 --> 00:02:49,116
How long as he been
watching you?

63
00:02:50,090 --> 00:02:51,479
My guess...

64
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:54,006
since I stopped communications
a few days ago.

65
00:02:55,339 --> 00:02:57,519
You worried about what we're
going to find out there?

66
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:59,719
- You're not.
- We can handle him.

67
00:03:00,259 --> 00:03:03,037
It's you and me.
Let's get to work.

68
00:03:07,624 --> 00:03:09,456
My grandmother
went fast than this

69
00:03:09,457 --> 00:03:11,000
and she didn't
even have a car.

70
00:03:11,135 --> 00:03:13,219
We have to take it easy,
we only have half a tank.

71
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:14,974
Well, hopefully we'll make it
to Flint Springs. It's got...

72
00:03:14,975 --> 00:03:16,402
Hopefully? What do you
mean "hopefully"?

73
00:03:16,403 --> 00:03:18,502
It's got a river.
It's prime white-tailed terrain.

74
00:03:18,521 --> 00:03:19,659
I know, but...
This is crazy.

75
00:03:19,660 --> 00:03:21,627
I told you that
I can't hunt.

76
00:03:21,628 --> 00:03:22,862
Now you want me to kill Bambi.

77
00:03:22,863 --> 00:03:24,136
You're gonna have to
learn, all right?

78
00:03:24,137 --> 00:03:26,142
Everyone's doing their part.
Bonnie's been out twice.

79
00:03:26,143 --> 00:03:27,425
Well, good for
frickin' Bonnie.

80
00:03:27,426 --> 00:03:28,775
Bonnie grew up on farm.

81
00:03:28,776 --> 00:03:30,511
The closest I ever got
to the outdoors

82
00:03:30,512 --> 00:03:32,673
was the is the Ralph Lauren
section of Neiman Marcus.

83
00:03:32,706 --> 00:03:33,849
There you go,
bargain hunting.

84
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:35,064
Same thing, but with a gun.

85
00:03:35,065 --> 00:03:37,080
Bargains? At Neimans?

86
00:03:37,646 --> 00:03:38,456
Sometimes I forget

87
00:03:38,457 --> 00:03:40,636
that the biggest designer
in your closet is Wrangler.

88
00:03:42,314 --> 00:03:43,404
What are you
laughing at?

89
00:03:43,510 --> 00:03:45,671
I've never seen you in a
domestic squabble before.

90
00:03:45,672 --> 00:03:47,441
Knock it off.
This isn't squabbling.

91
00:03:51,936 --> 00:03:52,901
Oh, my God.

92
00:03:56,197 --> 00:03:58,030
These dogs have tags.

93
00:04:03,371 --> 00:04:04,644
Look at all this.

94
00:04:09,394 --> 00:04:10,628
Wall Drugs.

95
00:04:11,091 --> 00:04:12,442
Wall, South Dakota.

96
00:04:12,518 --> 00:04:14,962
Do you think that's where all
these people were coming from?

97
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:15,895
Think about it.

98
00:04:16,208 --> 00:04:18,755
South Dakota without heat,
electricity, or...

99
00:04:19,314 --> 00:04:20,626
food being trucked in.

100
00:04:20,645 --> 00:04:22,575
It's got to be even worse
in North Dakota,

101
00:04:22,576 --> 00:04:23,481
Montana.

102
00:04:27,242 --> 00:04:28,438
Oh, my God.

103
00:04:40,826 --> 00:04:43,605
I read about this
at Blackjack.

104
00:04:44,369 --> 00:04:48,150
Mass migration, hundreds...
maybe thousands of people

105
00:04:48,883 --> 00:04:50,041
heading south.

106
00:04:52,221 --> 00:04:53,706
Trying to outrun winter.

107
00:04:54,919 --> 00:04:56,694
Should we be doing
that, too?

108
00:05:09,502 --> 00:05:12,492
Season 1 - Episode 14
" Heart Of Winter "

109
00:05:12,493 --> 00:05:14,494
[ Transcript ]
swsub.com

110
00:05:14,495 --> 00:05:16,500
[ Synchro ]
mOOchie / Loky / aSpro5oo

111
00:05:16,501 --> 00:05:19,490
[ www.seriessub.com ]

112
00:05:21,932 --> 00:05:23,109
How far is it?

113
00:05:25,154 --> 00:05:26,177
...60.

114
00:05:26,794 --> 00:05:28,048
It's about 60 yards.

115
00:05:28,781 --> 00:05:32,938
So 60 yard with almost
1.5 people per yard.

116
00:05:32,939 --> 00:05:34,075
That's 90.

117
00:05:34,076 --> 00:05:36,063
That's almost 100 people
just across.

118
00:05:36,078 --> 00:05:37,361
The way the ground
is trampled,

119
00:05:37,362 --> 00:05:39,290
you got to figure five
or tens times that amount

120
00:05:39,291 --> 00:05:40,408
of people came through here.

121
00:05:40,409 --> 00:05:43,535
Almost a thousand people?
Where are they going?

122
00:05:44,383 --> 00:05:46,216
South Texas, Mexico.

123
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,715
Anyplace warmer.

124
00:05:47,985 --> 00:05:49,895
It'd take weeks
to get there by foot.

125
00:05:49,904 --> 00:05:52,093
God know how many thousand
people have the same idea.

126
00:05:52,094 --> 00:05:53,734
Mexico's borders
could be closed.

127
00:05:53,735 --> 00:05:55,914
We don't even know if
there still is a Mexico.

128
00:05:57,112 --> 00:05:58,521
Maybe we should try
to catch on with them.

129
00:05:58,522 --> 00:06:02,399
We can barely feed ourselves,
let alone... hundreds more.

130
00:06:04,789 --> 00:06:05,908
We got to keep going.

131
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:09,574
Let's go.

132
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:20,482
Excuse me.
I'll be right back.

133
00:06:24,264 --> 00:06:25,470
Hey. Glad you came down.

134
00:06:26,212 --> 00:06:27,081
Thank you.

135
00:06:27,696 --> 00:06:29,490
- What time did you, uh...
- Early...

136
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:30,918
late, I guess.

137
00:06:30,984 --> 00:06:33,039
I didn't want to wake you,
you looked so peaceful.

138
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:34,699
Peaceful? Really?

139
00:06:34,796 --> 00:06:37,487
Did you have another one of those
bad dreams? Keep on there.

140
00:06:37,668 --> 00:06:39,723
I guess neither one of
us got much sleep.

141
00:06:40,539 --> 00:06:43,365
All I could do was think about
all these people down here, you know.

142
00:06:43,491 --> 00:06:46,076
And then I remembered about the
clothes we had in the attic.

143
00:06:46,077 --> 00:06:47,730
I thought that sweater
looked familiar.

144
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:49,711
Yeah, that woman was on
layover in Kansas City

145
00:06:49,712 --> 00:06:50,714
when the bombs went off,

146
00:06:51,061 --> 00:06:53,400
Her husband and two kids
were waiting for her at home.

147
00:06:53,434 --> 00:06:54,244
Where?

148
00:06:54,283 --> 00:06:55,209
Denver.

149
00:06:57,061 --> 00:06:58,547
I lead these people here.

150
00:06:58,665 --> 00:07:00,594
For better or worse
this is their home now.

151
00:07:00,671 --> 00:07:02,735
It's on me to make sure
they're taken care of.

152
00:07:03,546 --> 00:07:05,186
Yeah, of course.

153
00:07:06,073 --> 00:07:07,443
What can I do to help, huh?

154
00:07:08,769 --> 00:07:11,161
Talk to them,
follow your instincts.

155
00:07:12,222 --> 00:07:13,399
The truth is...

156
00:07:13,495 --> 00:07:15,290
I'm winging this myself.

157
00:07:23,233 --> 00:07:24,371
I'll be outside.
Here.

158
00:07:30,390 --> 00:07:32,107
Should be back
before dark.

159
00:07:33,439 --> 00:07:34,654
And if you're not?

160
00:07:37,823 --> 00:07:39,868
Just tell me when I
should start to worry.

161
00:07:40,196 --> 00:07:41,566
This is the last time,

162
00:07:41,817 --> 00:07:42,646
okay?

163
00:07:43,610 --> 00:07:44,942
After today

164
00:07:45,385 --> 00:07:46,562
I'm here...

165
00:07:48,588 --> 00:07:49,880
for good, huh?

166
00:07:51,413 --> 00:07:52,262
Okay.

167
00:07:52,879 --> 00:07:54,442
I'll hold you to that.

168
00:08:05,723 --> 00:08:06,533
Hi, honey.

169
00:08:07,150 --> 00:08:08,375
How'd it go this morning?

170
00:08:08,597 --> 00:08:09,871
The whole thing
was a bust.

171
00:08:09,909 --> 00:08:11,163
I'm sorry, hon.

172
00:08:11,288 --> 00:08:12,253
Jake's out there now.

173
00:08:12,254 --> 00:08:13,411
Hopefully he and Stanley

174
00:08:13,412 --> 00:08:14,916
will have better luck
than I did.

175
00:08:15,195 --> 00:08:15,996
Is April here?

176
00:08:15,997 --> 00:08:17,047
No, she's at
the clinic.

177
00:08:17,048 --> 00:08:18,995
She promised me
she'd take a nap.

178
00:08:19,198 --> 00:08:21,706
I hope it is warmer in that
clinic than it is in this house.

179
00:08:21,707 --> 00:08:23,712
I think this house has
dropped ten degrees

180
00:08:23,713 --> 00:08:24,792
in the last hour.

181
00:08:25,622 --> 00:08:27,339
Feels like a storm's
coming in.

182
00:08:28,564 --> 00:08:31,496
We'd better seal up these
windows the best was we can.

183
00:08:31,632 --> 00:08:33,754
Been going around collecting
old sheets and linens.

184
00:08:33,755 --> 00:08:36,031
We'll shove them
underneath the doors.

185
00:08:36,340 --> 00:08:37,613
Look what I found...

186
00:08:37,960 --> 00:08:39,639
hidden in Jake's closet.

187
00:08:41,819 --> 00:08:43,719
Lord knows how long
that's been there.

188
00:08:43,815 --> 00:08:45,918
Well, at least he was
drinking the good stuff.

189
00:08:45,957 --> 00:08:48,735
I used to hide the most awful
rotgut in the world

190
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:50,394
behind my mother's
china cabinet.

191
00:08:55,599 --> 00:08:56,621
What do you think?

192
00:08:58,107 --> 00:08:59,477
On an empty stomach?

193
00:09:00,210 --> 00:09:01,483
I'll get the glasses.

194
00:10:04,663 --> 00:10:06,506
Why would anyone destroy all this.

195
00:10:06,517 --> 00:10:09,601
If they'd wanted it out of commission,
they could have just taken it.

196
00:10:09,616 --> 00:10:11,576
Be worth a fortune after the E.M.P.

197
00:10:12,209 --> 00:10:13,839
Maybe there wasn't time,

198
00:10:13,903 --> 00:10:16,486
or maybe they didn't
care about this stuff.

199
00:10:23,866 --> 00:10:25,808
- How long?
- A couple of days...

200
00:10:25,899 --> 00:10:26,960
Give or take.

201
00:10:27,457 --> 00:10:29,466
But we just heard
from him yesterday.

202
00:10:31,228 --> 00:10:32,800
We heard from someone.

203
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:34,234
Remote uplink.

204
00:10:34,604 --> 00:10:36,800
Somebody else using
his access codes.

205
00:10:36,823 --> 00:10:38,534
Who could have done this?

206
00:10:46,597 --> 00:10:48,268
Wager for the first kill.

207
00:10:48,834 --> 00:10:50,417
I'm in for a dozen eggs.

208
00:10:51,689 --> 00:10:53,255
Two hours chopping wood.

209
00:10:53,602 --> 00:10:55,244
Tax return consultation.

210
00:10:57,096 --> 00:10:59,379
Oh, how about
foot massages for a week?

211
00:10:59,772 --> 00:11:01,275
For me, not for him.

212
00:11:02,252 --> 00:11:03,270
We'll talk.

213
00:11:03,293 --> 00:11:04,524
Stanley, stop.

214
00:11:10,334 --> 00:11:13,016
- What are they doing?
- They're blocking the whole road.

215
00:11:13,074 --> 00:11:14,831
More like staking it out.

216
00:11:16,073 --> 00:11:17,553
All right, turn around.

217
00:11:17,559 --> 00:11:18,918
And... and go where?

218
00:11:18,919 --> 00:11:22,773
I don't know. Just do it, all right?
Turn around. We'll find another road.

219
00:11:42,192 --> 00:11:43,961
I see it. Damn it.

220
00:11:48,427 --> 00:11:50,288
Why are they following us?

221
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,216
Stanley, gun it!

222
00:12:06,580 --> 00:12:07,968
This should get us
back to the highway.

223
00:12:07,969 --> 00:12:08,836
Then what?

224
00:12:08,837 --> 00:12:11,094
We try to make it back home,
find the patrol.

225
00:12:11,422 --> 00:12:13,302
Maybe they'll give up by then
or run out of gas.

226
00:12:13,313 --> 00:12:14,984
Yeah, if we don't first.

227
00:12:15,424 --> 00:12:17,289
Stanley...
Stanley, hold on!

228
00:12:19,116 --> 00:12:21,100
Doesn't look like
he put up much of a fight.

229
00:12:21,101 --> 00:12:22,852
He was probably out
before he knew what hit him.

230
00:12:22,853 --> 00:12:25,103
He must have trusted whoever did it.

231
00:12:25,438 --> 00:12:28,698
The thing is, whoever it was,

232
00:12:29,507 --> 00:12:31,669
they knew what
they were doing there,

233
00:12:31,938 --> 00:12:33,210
not over here.

234
00:12:33,349 --> 00:12:35,707
I mean, look at this.
It's a mess.

235
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:38,478
But the drives...
They look like they're still intact.

236
00:12:38,479 --> 00:12:41,719
The old man had information
on the entire team...

237
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:43,728
Contact information,
backgrounds...

238
00:12:43,729 --> 00:12:45,244
Last known whereabouts.

239
00:12:46,715 --> 00:12:48,796
Let's find out where everybody is.

240
00:12:51,392 --> 00:12:52,707
We can't outrun them.

241
00:12:52,708 --> 00:12:54,694
- How far till Jericho?
- Too far.

242
00:12:56,709 --> 00:12:57,720
Oh, God!

243
00:13:06,766 --> 00:13:07,783
Stay down.

244
00:13:15,037 --> 00:13:16,181
Stay down.

245
00:13:35,172 --> 00:13:36,994
Give me that drive you got there.

246
00:13:37,813 --> 00:13:39,670
Must feel good to be back
in the saddle, huh?

247
00:13:40,218 --> 00:13:42,818
I wish we didn't have
to come out here in the first place.

248
00:13:42,819 --> 00:13:45,748
What, are you getting soft on me?
Too much domestic bliss?

249
00:13:45,749 --> 00:13:47,345
Not quite bliss.

250
00:13:48,683 --> 00:13:51,219
There.
There it is. We're in.

251
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:16,951
Thank you.

252
00:14:18,367 --> 00:14:20,158
Karaoke bullfighter, right?

253
00:14:20,159 --> 00:14:21,215
Excuse me?

254
00:14:21,216 --> 00:14:22,730
At that bar in Barcelona.

255
