be in the woods together.

282
00:16:07,275 --> 00:16:11,137
I was always afraid that Jake
would forget about that.

283
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:14,478
You know, that he'd grow up only
remembering the bad times. That we were

284
00:16:16,521 --> 00:16:19,647
That he wouldn't remember
that we had been close.

285
00:16:19,648 --> 00:16:24,046
That we were... buddies once.

286
00:16:28,724 --> 00:16:29,961
He remembers...

287
00:16:34,354 --> 00:16:35,614
deep down.

288
00:16:38,107 --> 00:16:40,824
That's why you mean
so much to him.

289
00:16:43,853 --> 00:16:45,691
Boy, that wind sounds awful.

290
00:16:47,460 --> 00:16:50,015
I hope Stanley and Jake
are okay out there.

291
00:17:44,768 --> 00:17:45,829
What happened?

292
00:17:46,410 --> 00:17:48,104
Jake, Stanley's not moving.

293
00:17:48,133 --> 00:17:50,110
- What?
- Stanley's not moving.

294
00:17:58,438 --> 00:17:59,847
Oh, my God. Go hide.

295
00:18:01,548 --> 00:18:02,732
- Go hide.
- No

296
00:18:03,017 --> 00:18:04,228
- Go on.
- No, No. Stanley...

297
00:18:04,229 --> 00:18:06,104
You'll be fine.
Go! Go hide!

298
00:19:24,843 --> 00:19:26,790
Come on.
Help me with Stanley.

299
00:19:28,599 --> 00:19:29,704
I can't move.

300
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,446
Ritts, Woodworth, Pierce.

301
00:19:36,383 --> 00:19:37,423
That's half the team.

302
00:19:37,862 --> 00:19:40,140
We're being hunted.
It's worse than that.

303
00:19:41,134 --> 00:19:42,724
It's Woodworth and his wife.

304
00:19:43,082 --> 00:19:45,247
They were in Richmond.
That's his daughter.

305
00:19:45,672 --> 00:19:47,833
Anyone close to us
is in danger, too.

306
00:19:48,168 --> 00:19:49,371
No loose ends.

307
00:19:50,115 --> 00:19:51,349
Don't worry about your family.

308
00:19:51,369 --> 00:19:53,467
