that hasn't changed.

347
00:22:20,326 --> 00:22:21,792
The one constant.

348
00:22:22,351 --> 00:22:23,316
I love you.

349
00:22:24,282 --> 00:22:25,903
And it's going
to take a whole lot more

350
00:22:25,904 --> 00:22:27,948
than the end of the world
to change that.

351
00:22:39,335 --> 00:22:41,747
- How are your legs?
- I don't know I can't feel anything.

352
00:22:42,615 --> 00:22:43,695
The ground's
frozen solid.

353
00:22:43,696 --> 00:22:44,967
It's sucking the heat
right out of you.

354
00:22:44,968 --> 00:22:46,261
Why can't we build a fire?

355
00:22:46,338 --> 00:22:47,688
You smell the fumes?

356
00:22:47,862 --> 00:22:49,618
You have to get back to town.

357
00:22:49,753 --> 00:22:51,199
All right. I'm going
to try and go.

358
00:22:52,206 --> 00:22:53,904
No. You can't on that ankle.

359
00:22:54,276 --> 00:22:56,258
- I'll go.
