360
00:22:56,259 --> 00:22:57,512
They went the other way.

361
00:22:57,608 --> 00:23:00,290
Jericho has a patrol
five miles out of town.

362
00:23:00,386 --> 00:23:01,872
We can't have come
more than ten.

363
00:23:01,968 --> 00:23:03,435
Jake, it's too dangerous.

364
00:23:03,485 --> 00:23:04,527
What are our options?

365
00:23:04,546 --> 00:23:05,916
With no bags, no fire?

366
00:23:05,993 --> 00:23:08,386
All right, one of you goes
or we all die here.

367
00:23:12,746 --> 00:23:14,443
All right, fine, fine.

368
00:23:15,628 --> 00:23:18,737
I threw a flashlight over there
somewhere. You might need it.

369
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:22,323
Listen...

370
00:23:23,557 --> 00:23:25,815
stay on the shoulder
the whole time, okay?

371
00:23:26,135 --> 00:23:28,643
If you see any headlights
or you hear any engines,

372
00:23:29,916 --> 00:23:31,325
get low and hide,

373
00:23:31,421 --> 00:23:33,215
all right?
Now, you're gonna
want to head

374
00:23:33,732 --> 00:23:34,725
southeast.

375
00:23:35,863 --> 00:23:38,217
Stanley, that doesn't mean
anything to me.

376
00:23:41,072 --> 00:23:42,423
Stay on this road.

377
00:23:42,538 --> 00:23:44,159
Stay on this road
and then you make...

378
00:23:44,216 --> 00:23:45,683
make your first left

379
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,747
Okay?
And you're gonna go about a mile

