get back on the move.

396
00:24:39,430 --> 00:24:41,089
I am not leaving them alone.

397
00:24:41,090 --> 00:24:42,825
- I don't think you have a choice.
- No...

398
00:24:42,826 --> 00:24:45,063
See, because I've got leverage.

399
00:24:45,526 --> 00:24:48,458
If they kill me, they will
never find the package.

400
00:24:48,843 --> 00:24:50,599
It's not you
they're gonna kill.

401
00:24:51,004 --> 00:24:53,724
It'll be Sam
or Darcy or me;

402
00:24:54,901 --> 00:24:57,409
anything they can use
to get to you.

403
00:25:01,983 --> 00:25:04,375
Anything they can
use to get to me.

404
00:25:08,666 --> 00:25:09,843
The body.

405
00:25:10,682 --> 00:25:13,151
These... These, uh...

406
00:25:14,237 --> 00:25:17,806
...these half-smashed drives,

407
00:25:18,732 --> 00:25:20,700
<i>...this whole...</i>

408
00:25:21,086 --> 00:25:22,436
this whole setup--

409
00:25:22,957 --> 00:25:24,693
If someone had wanted
to destroy all this,

410
00:25:24,694 --> 00:25:26,304
why leave the house
standing, huh?

411
00:25:26,516 --> 00:25:28,542
Why not just burn it all down?

412
00:25:29,207 --> 00:25:31,060
Someone wanted us
to see all this.

413
00:25:39,956 --> 00:25:41,229
We're being played.

414
00:25:41,866 --> 00:25:43,708
