485
00:29:42,736 --> 00:29:45,089
Hell, you can fly us
there yourself, huh?

486
00:29:45,090 --> 00:29:47,722
Come on. Come on.
Tell me something good, man.

487
00:29:47,723 --> 00:29:50,786
I haven't talked to you in five years.
You've been gone for five years.

488
00:29:51,919 --> 00:29:54,061
Tell me... Hey, tell me
about San Diego.

489
00:29:54,062 --> 00:29:55,166
How was it?

490
00:29:56,130 --> 00:29:57,924
- Warm.
- Warm, right.

491
00:29:58,561 --> 00:30:00,375
Beaches, blondes, huh?

492
00:30:01,543 --> 00:30:03,144
What were you doing there?

493
00:30:03,222 --> 00:30:05,324
Flying, flying planes.

494
00:30:05,402 --> 00:30:08,083
Really?
That's cool, man.

495
00:30:08,160 --> 00:30:10,649
Your grandfather
would've been psyched, huh?

496
00:30:10,758 --> 00:30:13,246
Did you have a girl there?
I know you had a girl.

497
00:30:13,594 --> 00:30:15,002
She's dead.

498
00:30:20,736 --> 00:30:21,971
What do you mean?

499
00:30:22,762 --> 00:30:24,247
You don't know that.

500
00:30:24,248 --> 00:30:27,131
I mean, it all depends on where she was
when the bombs went off, right?

501
00:30:27,132 --> 00:30:28,717
I mean, she could
have made it, right?

502
00:30:28,736 --> 00:30:30,617
- Tell me what her name was.
- She's dead....

503
00:30:30,618 --> 00:30:31,871
It was my fault.

504
00:30:31,872 --> 00:30:33,538
- It's not your fault.
- Let me lay down.

505
00:30:33,539 --> 00:30:34,793
- Jake, no.
- Let me lay down.

506
00:30:34,794 --> 00:30:36,665
It wasn't your fault.
Come on... Come on...

507
00:30:36,915 --> 00:30:38,816
Come on, stay with me.
You gotta stay with me.

508
00:30:40,320 --> 00:30:42,327
Come on, Jake.

509
00:30:42,619 --> 00:30:44,568
Stay with me, Jake.
Come on, man.

510
00:30:47,558 --> 00:30:48,773
Stay with me.

