00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:20,016
Gotta keep moving.

514
00:31:45,229 --> 00:31:47,949
Please don't hurt me...
please don't hurt me.

515
00:31:47,988 --> 00:31:49,512
Please don't hurt me!

516
00:31:49,820 --> 00:31:51,229
Please don't hurt me...

517
00:31:51,576 --> 00:31:52,603
Mimi?

518
00:31:55,839 --> 00:31:58,771
- It's Gail and Johnston Green, honey.
You're safe.  - Oh, thanks God!

519
00:31:58,974 --> 00:32:00,682
Come on, baby,
let's get out of here.

520
00:32:01,010 --> 00:32:02,052
Come on.

521
00:32:10,231 --> 00:32:11,582
Those are hideous.

522
00:32:11,583 --> 00:32:13,588
Are those the sheets
from your old apartment?

523
00:32:13,935 --> 00:32:16,251
Because you can't expect
anyone to sleep on those.

524
00:32:16,709 --> 00:32:19,680
If anyone asks, we'll pretend
someone else donated them.

525
00:32:28,921 --> 00:32:29,943
Your dress.

526
00:32:32,528 --> 00:32:34,149
Guess I shouldn't be seeing this, huh?

527
00:32:35,615 --> 00:32:37,737
The day's sort of come and gone, so...

528
00:32:39,665 --> 00:32:40,765
It'll come again.

529
00:32:41,479 --> 00:32:42,482
You think?

530
00:32:44,258 --> 00:32:45,377
I do.

531
00:32:46,843 --> 00:32:48,869
I tell you what, I've got
a pack of Ramen noodles

532
00:32:48,870 --> 00:32:50,470
with your name on it,
what do you say?

533
00:32:50,894 --> 00:32:53,788
Great. I'll deliver this to the shelter
and come back and wash up.

534
00:32:54,347 --> 00:32:55,756
Roger, wait.

535
00:32:57,433 --> 00:32:58,803
I'll come with you.

536
00:33:15,376 --> 00:33:17,035
It's Mom and Dad, honey!

537
00:33:17,671 --> 00:33:19,523
Stanley, you all right, sweetheart?

538
00:33:20,448 --> 00:33:22,551
You need to go get in the truck
and get warm, pal.

539
00:33:22,552 --> 00:33:24,230
- Where's Mimi?
- I'm right here.

540
00:33:24,289 --> 00:33:25,601
Stanley, I'm right here.

541
00:33:28,282 --> 00:33:30,192
Wake up. Wake up!

542
00:33:31,041 --> 00:33:32,237
Wake up, Jake.

543
00:33:32,642 --> 00:33:33,645
Wake up.

544
00:33:33,950 --> 00:33:35,050
Wake up. Oh, thank God.

545
00:33:35,051 --> 00:33:36,400
We're gonna help you, honey.

546
00:33:38,619 --> 00:33:39,950
We saw the storm coming

547
00:33:40,259 --> 00:33:42,420
and we started to worry
when you hadn't come back.

548
00:33:42,421 --> 00:33:43,519
Sweetheart...

549
00:33:46,259 --> 00:33:47,108
Honey,

550
00:33:47,109 --> 00:33:49,326
we're not gonna be able
to get this truck off of him.

551
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:51,216
I need you to take
these guys back to town

552
00:33:51,217 --> 00:33:52,725
and get me some help out here.

553
00:33:52,726 --> 00:33:55,383
You signal when you're coming back
so I know it's you, all right?

554
00:33:55,384 --> 00:33:57,794
- I'll flash the lights.
- All right, go, go, go!

555
00:33:59,972 --> 00:34:01,400
Jake, look at me, son.

556
00:34:01,401 --> 00:34:02,403
Lookie here.

557
00:34:02,711 --> 00:34:04,930
You're gonna make it, son...
I know you.

558
00:34:05,914 --> 00:34:08,615
I know what you're made of.
You're gonna be all right.

559
00:34:09,155 --> 00:34:11,759
You're gonna make it.
Stay with me now.

560
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:27,904
Robert, please,
the kids are sleeping.

561
00:34:28,463 --> 00:34:31,029
- I'm sorry.
- What on earth are you doing?

562
00:34:31,372 --> 00:34:32,896
Oh, I'm sorry.

563
00:34:45,650 --> 00:34:47,521
Jake, you'll be home real soon,

564
00:34:47,927 --> 00:34:50,010
but you got to stay
with me now. Come on.

565
00:34:52,373 --> 00:34:54,216
Leave me here.
Leave me alone.

566
00:34:54,486 --> 00:34:56,145
Now, I'm not going anywhere.

567
00:34:56,705 --> 00:34:58,267
But you got to hang on.

568
00:34:58,576 --> 00:35:00,467
Now, they'll be here soon, son.

569
00:35:02,512 --> 00:35:03,524
Dad...

570
00:35:04,141 --> 00:35:05,386
I'm sorry.

571
00:35:06,231 --> 00:35:08,353
Oh, son, you got nothing
to be sorry about.

572
00:35:13,177 --> 00:35:15,125
Open your eyes, Jake.
Come on, now.

573
00:35:15,974 --> 00:35:18,116
Look at me.
Look at me, Jake.

574
00:35:20,392 --> 00:35:21,878
I can see her.

575
00:35:23,923 --> 00:35:25,061
See who?

576
00:35:26,662 --> 00:35:28,032
The girl.

577
00:35:30,327 --> 00:35:31,967
What... girl?

578
00:35:31,968 --> 00:35:33,704
Jake, I think you're hallucinating, son.

579
00:35:33,705 --> 00:35:34,727
No, listen to me.

580
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:38,836
When I was in Iraq...

581
00:35:41,248 --> 00:35:42,849
... there was a girl.

582
00:35:45,184 --> 00:35:46,901
She couldn't have been more than...

583
00:35:47,592 --> 00:35:48,749
10 or 12...

584
00:35:49,656 --> 00:35:51,007
Don't talk now, son.

585
00:35:51,199 --> 00:35:52,222
You save your energy.

586
00:35:52,223 --> 00:35:53,843
We'll talk when we get... home.

587
00:35:55,155 --> 00:35:56,659
I killed her, Dad.

588
00:36:02,544 --> 00:36:04,241
I killed a little girl.

589
00:36:27,636 --> 00:36:28,967
Hurry up!

590
00:36:42,008 --> 00:36:43,494
Open your eyes, Jake.

591
00:36:43,495 --> 00:36:44,864
Open your eyes.

592
00:36:46,156 --> 00:36:47,930
All right, everyone on three...

593
00:36:47,931 --> 00:36:48,934
One,

594
00:36:49,262 --> 00:36:50,747
two, three!

595
00:36:56,090 --> 00:36:57,190
All right, he's free.

596
00:36:57,692 --> 00:36:58,984
Let's get the board in here.

597
00:36:59,988 --> 00:37:01,821
One, two, three.

598
00:37:12,740 --> 00:37:13,763
You were right.

599
00:37:13,764 --> 00:37:16,695
I need to get my family
as far away from me as possible.

600
00:37:17,602 --> 00:37:19,106
I've been thinking, and...

601
00:37:19,897 --> 00:37:21,557
There's no other choice.

602
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:24,817
You're doing the right thing.

603
00:37:26,264 --> 00:37:27,344
Listen.

604
00:37:29,274 --> 00:37:30,663
After they're safe,

605
00:37:31,184 --> 00:37:33,036
you and me need
to get back in the field.

606
00:37:33,537 --> 00:37:35,466
That's half our team gone, Sarah,

607
00:37:35,467 --> 00:37:37,681
and whoever did that
did it for a reason.

608
00:37:40,671 --> 00:37:42,350
How are you gonna tell Darcy?

609
00:37:45,416 --> 00:37:47,211
I'll tell her after I've moved them.

610
00:37:48,445 --> 00:37:51,108
She'll never agree if she knows
I won't be staying with them.

611
00:38:01,835 --> 00:38:03,764
He's better off here
than the med center.

612
00:38:04,015 --> 00:38:07,140
We're still on emergency power,
and it's... it's warmer here.

613
00:38:08,703 --> 00:38:10,034
Here, honey.

614
00:38:10,671 --> 00:38:11,921
What about his injuries?

615
00:38:11,922 --> 00:38:13,835
Well, the cut on his head
isn't very deep,

616
00:38:13,836 --> 00:38:15,972
and neither one
of his legs are broken.

617
00:38:16,705 --> 00:38:17,920
He's very lucky.

618
00:38:17,921 --> 00:38:19,232
I'm freezing.

619
00:38:19,657 --> 00:38:21,470
I'm gonna go get you
some more blankets.

620
00:38:21,952 --> 00:38:23,476
You're still hypothermic.

621
00:38:23,477 --> 00:38:26,486
It's just gonna take a few hours
for your body to stabilize.

622
00:38:28,183 --> 00:38:30,325
- Can we have a minute?
- Oh, sure.

623
00:38:45,759 --> 00:38:47,052
Dad...

624
00:38:51,701 --> 00:38:53,245
What I told you out there...

625
00:38:56,139 --> 00:38:57,721
please forget it.

626
00:38:59,419 --> 00:39:00,576
Please.

627
00:39:04,338 --> 00:39:05,766
Afraid I can't do that.

628
00:39:18,129 --> 00:39:20,483
I've seen a lot of things
in my time, Jake.

629
00:39:22,837 --> 00:39:24,052
I've been to war.

630
00:39:25,364 --> 00:39:28,740
I know what war can do.
I know what men can do... Terrible...

631
00:39:30,149 --> 00:39:31,635
... terrible things.

632
00:39:34,542 --> 00:39:35,893
I know what I did.

633
00:39:38,555 --> 00:39:40,060
You can talk to me.

634
00:40:05,526 --> 00:40:06,934
When you're ready, son.

635
00:40:10,273 --> 00:40:11,488
When you're ready.

636
00:40:29,527 --> 00:40:30,896
You okay?

637
00:40:39,192 --> 00:40:40,465
How's the sprain?

638
00:40:42,009 --> 00:40:45,038
I think it'd be better with painkillers,
but I'm not gonna complain.

639
00:40:45,944 --> 00:40:49,066
You know, for a while there, I didn't
think I'd ever feel anything again.

640
00:40:51,960 --> 00:40:53,464
When I was out there,

641
00:40:53,985 --> 00:40:55,317
just for a moment,

642
00:40:56,378 --> 00:40:58,153
I didn't think
I was gonna make it.

643
00:40:59,196 --> 00:41:01,859
And I stopped... to rest.

644
00:41:02,746 --> 00:41:05,235
And then I just didn't
even want to move.

645
00:41:08,823 --> 00:41:10,000
But you did.

646
00:41:11,505 --> 00:41:12,817
You did make it.

647
00:41:14,283 --> 00:41:15,846
And I knew you would.

648
00:41:22,501 --> 00:41:24,373
Your lips are still cold.

649
00:41:26,668 --> 00:41:28,520
Maybe you can warm them.

650
00:41:33,112 --> 00:41:35,369
That's the worst line
I've ever heard.

651
00:41:35,890 --> 00:41:37,800
I know. I've got others.

652
00:41:39,035 --> 00:41:40,636
- Shut up.
- Okay.

653
00:41:51,465 --> 00:41:52,798
Tomorrow morning...

654
00:41:54,959 --> 00:41:56,033
we're leaving.

655
00:41:57,342 --> 00:41:59,170
We're leaving?
For... for where?

656
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:02,318
I don't know yet.

657
00:42:03,380 --> 00:42:04,552
You don't know?

658
00:42:09,060 --> 00:42:11,504
Darcy, when I came
to get you in DC...

659
00:42:13,616 --> 00:42:15,283
I told you it wasn't safe,

660
00:42:15,900 --> 00:42:17,506
but I couldn't tell you why.

661
00:42:23,038 --> 00:42:24,236
I'm going for a walk.

662
00:42:37,589 --> 00:42:39,396
I have something
in my possession.

663
00:42:41,610 --> 00:42:43,426
And there's people
out there that want it,

664
00:42:43,981 --> 00:42:46,154
that will stop at nothing to get it.

665
00:42:48,471 --> 00:42:50,071
And that puts you,
me and the kids

666
00:42:50,466 --> 00:42:51,592
in danger here.

667
00:42:57,746 --> 00:42:59,850
Okay, so th... then we go.

668
00:43:01,193 --> 00:43:02,398
<i>I trust you.</i>

669
00:43:08,107 --> 00:43:09,272
<i>Robert, do y...</i>

670
00:43:10,725 --> 00:43:11,792
Do you trust me?

671
00:43:14,785 --> 00:43:17,068
- You're late.
- You're impatient.

672
00:43:22,361 --> 00:43:23,852
Then listen to me.

673
00:43:24,731 --> 00:43:26,895
Okay, Sarah is not on our side.

674
00:43:27,359 --> 00:43:28,781
Now... whatever's...

675
00:43:29,284 --> 00:43:30,608
gone on between the two of you,

676
00:43:30,609 --> 00:43:32,929
I'm telling you, Robert,
she's not here to help us.

677
00:43:36,455 --> 00:43:37,937
Have you located the package?

678
00:43:38,648 --> 00:43:39,653
Soon.

679
00:43:41,096 --> 00:43:43,033
Hawkins is starting to put
the pieces together.

680
00:43:43,034 --> 00:43:45,562
- He needs to be eliminated.
- I know.

681
00:43:45,778 --> 00:43:48,683
We've already eliminated the other
three targets without incident.

682
00:43:48,684 --> 00:43:50,363
Why are you stalling on this one?

683
00:44:01,356 --> 00:44:03,124
Because this one is different.

684
00:44:03,475 --> 00:44:05,964
[ www.seriessub.com ]

